.TH MFUTIL-SYNC 1 2025-01-01 "mfutil 0.1.1"
.SH NAME
mfutil-sync \- Sync music tags with MusicBrainz and fetch cover art
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mfutil sync
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B sync
subcommand synchronizes music metadata with MusicBrainz database and
downloads cover artwork. It updates tags with accurate artist, album, and
track information, and fetches high-quality cover images.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-music-dir " " \fIPATH\fR
Specify the music directory path (default: ~/Music)
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help information
.SH FEATURES
.TP
Update artist and album metadata from MusicBrainz
.TP
Correct track titles and numbering
.TP
Fetch cover art from MusicBrainz
.TP
Batch processing with progress indication
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B MUSICBRAINZ_USER_AGENT
Custom user agent string for MusicBrainz API requests
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Sync metadata and art for default music directory:
.B mfutil sync
.TP
Sync metadata and art for custom directory:
.B mfutil sync --music-dir /path/to/music
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mfutil (1),
.BR mfutil-art (1),
.BR mfutil-all (1)
.SH NOTES
This command requires internet access to query MusicBrainz services.
Large libraries may take significant time to process.